title: Software Developer
job_description:
Job Description:
Software Developer
Jonas Software – Club Division
If you are looking for a fast-paced environment building something that millions of people use daily, then you’ll find it here with the Research and Development team at Jonas Club Software. Our goal is to deliver high quality software that meets the real world needs and exceeds our customers’ expectations.
Everyone should be a voice within the team; the best products come from collaboration and independent thinking, and we want your voice. We're looking for someone with great Web Development skills and experience, so they can help guide our younger developers and advance their careers.
We're looking for developers with wisdom to make critical software decisions, so that we are shipping high quality code relatively bug-free, and applications which are built with simplicity and practicality in mind. We want to keep our customers and developers happy and give ourselves the opportunities to develop innovative and essential products for our clients. http://www.jonasclub.com/About-Us/Jonas-Team.aspx.
THE POSITION
We are looking for someone who has a passion for growth and is eager to deliver high quality solutions to our clients from start to finish. You will be collaborating with multiple groups and individuals, while working in an agile environment to help bring ideas to life through design, analysis and implementation. The successful candidate will have strong problem-solving skills, creativity, strive for innovation, well developed technical learning and ability to learn on the fly.
Accountabilities
-  Provide status updates on work In Progress and Completed
-  Provide guidance on solutions with an ability to communicate to both technical and non-technical individuals
-  Act as an expert technical resource for solution design and implementation
-  Assure high-quality and security focused solutions
-  Be flexible and adaptable while keeping the Product and Customer in focus
-  Open-minded, positive attitude and superior problem-solving skills
Qualifications
-  5+ years building scalable, high volume Web Applications
-  Experience with ASP.NET Web Applications
-  Experience with building .NET/.NET Core Web API development with security principles in mind
-  Experience with RDBMS (MS SQL Server) including schema design, stored procedure creation and DB optimization
-  Experience using frontend frameworks (Angular, React, Vue, etc)
-  AngularJS is an asset
-  Strong knowledge of HTML, CSS, JavaScript
-  Knowledge of Blazor is an asset
-  Experience working with CI/CD pipeline tools such as JIRA and TeamCity
-  Experienced when working within a cross-functional team with varying skillsets
-  Excellent leadership, communication, and interpersonal skills

More About Jonas Software:
Jonas Software is the leading provider of enterprise management software solutions to the Country and Golf Clubs, Foodservice, Construction, Fitness & Sports, Attractions, Salon & Spa, Education, Radiology/Laboratory Information Systems, and Product Licensing industries. Within these vertical markets, Jonas is made up of over 65 distinct brands, which are respected and leaders within their own domain.
Jonas’ vision is to be the branded global leader across the aforementioned vertical markets and to be recognized by customers and respective industry stakeholders as the trusted provider of ‘Software for Life’ and as an ambassador for technology, product innovation, quality, and customer service.
Jonas Software is the valued technology partner of over 60,000 customers worldwide in more than 30 countries. Jonas employs over 2,000 skilled individuals consisting of a cross-section of industry experts and technology professionals. Jonas is headquartered in Canada and also operates offices throughout North America, the United Kingdom, Europe, Australia New Zealand and Africa. Jonas is a 100% owned subsidiary of Constellation Software Inc., headquartered in Toronto and traded on the S&P/TSX 60.
